# React/JSX Standards

## Escape Special Characters in JSX Text

Always escape these characters in JSX text content:

| Character | Use Instead |
|-----------|-------------|
| `'` (apostrophe) | `&apos;` |
| `"` (quote) | `&quot;` |
| `<` | `&lt;` |
| `>` | `&gt;` |

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - will cause build errors
<p>Let's go</p>
<p>It's working</p>

// ✅ GOOD
<p>Let&apos;s go</p>
<p>It&apos;s working</p>
```

## Why?
React's ESLint rules require escaping to prevent XSS vulnerabilities and ensure proper rendering.
